import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import './Statistics.css'; const Statistics = () => { const [totalChildren, setTotalChildren] = useState(0); const [maleChildren, setMaleChildren] = useState(0); const [femaleChildren, setFemaleChildren] = useState(0); const [vaccinatedChildren, setVaccinatedChildren] = useState({ after_birth: 0, first_month: 0, second_month: 0, fourth_month: 0, month_six: 0, months: 0, month: 0, }); useEffect(() => { fetch('http://localhost:3121/api/doctor/statistics/totalChildren') .then((response) => response.json()) .then((data) => setTotalChildren(data.totalChildren)); fetch('http://localhost:3121/api/doctor/statistics/maleChildren') .then((response) => response.json()) .then((data) => setMaleChildren(data.maleChildren)); fetch('http://localhost:3121/api/doctor/statistics/femaleChildren') .then((response) => response.json()) .then((data) => setFemaleChildren(data.femaleChildren)); fetch('http://localhost:3121/api/doctor/statistics/vaccinatedChildren') .then((response) => response.json()) .then((data) => setVaccinatedChildren(data)); }, []); return (

); }; export default Statistics;
